==English==

===Pronunciation===
*fāz, /feɪz/, /<tt>feIz</tt>/
*:'''Homophones''': [[phase]]
*:[[Rhymes:English:-eɪz|Rhymes: -eɪz]]

===Verb===
'''faze'''

# {{misspelling of|phase}}  To frighten or cause hesitation; to [[daunt]], [[put off]] (usually used in the negative)
#: ''Jumping out of an airplane does not '''faze''' him, yet he is afraid to ride a roller coaster.''

